OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1783792086
OL,3,CLongest-serving Archers actor Patricia
OL,4,CGreene dies aged 95
OL,6,FJeremy Howe, editor of The Archers,
OL,7,Fsaid: "Paddy (her nickname) was
OL,8,Futterly singular, a fabulous and
OL,9,Fraucously funny raconteur, and like
OL,10,Fthe best actors when on mic you were
OL,11,Fnever quite sure how she would play a
OL,12,Fscene, but you knew she would play it
OL,13,Fbrilliantly.
OL,15,F"Her portrayal of Jill Archer was
OL,16,Fformidable, but also wonderfully warm
OL,17,Fand loving, and enormous fun ` Paddy
OL,18,Fcould find a laugh in a simple 'but'.
OL,26,@oD@GOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,347,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1783792086
OL,3,CLongest-serving Archers actor Patricia
OL,4,CGreene dies aged 95
OL,6,F"It was an incredible privilege to
OL,7,Fwork with her and she will be greatly
OL,8,Fmissed by all of us within the
OL,9,Fproduction team, as well as by
OL,10,Fmillions of Archers listeners."
OL,12,FGreene's character was orphaned and
OL,13,Fbrought up by her aunt, and came to
OL,14,FAmbridge, where the soap is set.
OL,16,FThere she caught the eye of the
OL,17,Frecently widowed Phil Archer, played
OL,18,Fby Norman Painting, who proposed to
OL,19,Fher. At first she refused, but in 1957
OL,20,Fthe couple married.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@_O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,347,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1783792086
OL,3,CLongest-serving Archers actor Patricia
OL,4,CGreene dies aged 95
OL,6,FThe fictional couple had four
OL,7,Fchildren, twins Kenton and Shula,
OL,8,FDavid, and Elizabeth.
OL,10,FJill also acted as a member of the
OL,11,Fparish council and as a driving force
OL,12,Fin the women's institute on the show.
OL,14,FGreene was reportedly moved to a care
OL,15,Fhome in 2023, but continued to record
OL,16,FThe Archers.
OL,18,FMohit Bakaya, controller of BBC Radio
OL,19,F4, said: "Paddy's contribution to The
OL,20,FArchers over almost 70 years has been
OL,21,Foutstanding.
OL,26,@{D@JOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/8
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,347,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1783792086
OL,3,CLongest-serving Archers actor Patricia
OL,4,CGreene dies aged 95
OL,6,F"She has been a constant companion in
OL,7,FRadio 4 listeners' lives, and it has
OL,8,Fbeen a pleasure to hear her ever-
OL,9,Fevolving portrayal of Jill Archer over
OL,10,Fthe decades. She leaves a wonderful
OL,11,Flegacy.
OL,13,F"Ambridge will not be the same without
OL,14,Fher, and all of us here at Radio 4
OL,15,Fsend our love and condolences to her
OL,16,Ffamily at this difficult time."
OL,18,FGreene was born in 1931, and dreamed
OL,19,Fof becoming an actor at an early age.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUxD@_O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/8
