OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F346A1783792086
OL,3,CLongest-serving Archers actor Patricia
OL,4,CGreene dies aged 95
OL,6,FAfter a stint working in a sheet metal
OL,7,Ffactory and then as a ward orderly in
OL,8,Fa children's hospital, she trained at
OL,9,Fthe Royal Central School of Speech and
OL,10,FDrama in London, and later joined The
OL,11,FArchers.
OL,13,FAlongside The Archers, she also
OL,14,Fappeared in many radio and TV plays,
OL,15,Fand was in the film version of Arnold
OL,16,FWesker's The Kitchen.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/8
